    "sidebarcontentbottom": "[quote]I saw it with me own eyes. Out of nowhere, the sand shuddered away under my feet, my eyes following the direction it went and before long it was there — a gaping pit, a whirlpool of sand sucking in everything.\r\n\r\nI ran the other way as fast as my legs could carry me, but the sand was moving faster. The eye of the storm approached ever closer until all that remained was darkness and the slight glistening of gems and metals.\r\n\r\nHow I survived.. even I do not understand to this day. It felt like I was sleeping, just breathing as is, darkness all around me just when you're asleep. Until I felt something scathing my leg and suddenly I was dragged along. Before I knew it, there was light and I laid at the port of my village once more.|Grandpa telling his story to the village kids before bedtime[/quote]",
